race.comment: The well-related HIGHGROVE ROSE (15) (half to G2 winner Not An Option) is on the doorstep of a maiden victory with consecutive runner-up finishes this time in work and this is not an overly strong affair. Draws the inside marble and should be right there when the whips are cracking. ELROND (4) is yet to miss a drum in four spins around this circuit and will be rock-hard fit for this. Looms as the main danger. MISS HIGHFALUTIN (14) gets the deadly Gollan/Jones combination and only needs some luck from the wide draw to be playing a major role in the outcome. EXPRESS STAR (5) has placed three of five overall and gets some weight off with the 1.5kg claim. Top-three candidate. SEVILO (12) next in line from the low draw.
